    "Based on the Howey test, Bitcoin is not a security (specifically because it does not satisfy requirements two and four discussed above), but one could argue that many other cryptocurrencies (such as those featured in the cases we explore below) are.",
    "Notably, it is possible that a cryptocurrency's status as a security can change over time (Moffett 2022).",
